      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs italic text-ink-500">Prices as of June 2026; verify current. All prices exclude 18% GST. E-invoicing mandate: turnover above ₹5 crore (2026). QuickBooks India closed to new subscriptions (service ended 30 April 2023).</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-700"><strong>The honest take:</strong> if you're a small firm that just crossed the threshold, <strong>Zoho Books</strong> or <strong>Vyapar</strong> can get you compliant cheaply, and desktop practices may stay on <strong>TallyPrime</strong>. But if you want e-invoicing, e-way bills, returns and full accounting on one flat bill with unlimited users, <strong>Nidhi Books from ₹399/month</strong> is the best-value e-invoicing software for a growing Indian business.</p>
